## Part 2: Meta Ads (Facebook/Instagram) — PRIMARY PAID CHANNEL

Meta is the primary paid acquisition channel, focusing on demo generation and trial signups across all product lines.

**Annual Budget:** £41,000 (55% of total marketing spend)

**Note:** Financial model assumes marketing spend of 30% of revenue (£58,227 in Year 1), but this marketing plan allocates a fixed £75,000 budget to accelerate customer acquisition and build pipeline for Year 2.

**Why Meta (Not Google):**
- Better ROI: CPL £30 vs Google £50-70
- Larger addressable audience (not limited by search volume)
- Superior targeting (interests, behaviors, job titles)
- Visual creative advantages (video demos, before/after)

